2022, you were so good to us. You gave us a new home, career growth, travel, new friends, and overall another year to grow together and continue to create this beautiful life. 🤍🥹

Our first home project of 2023 is complete.✨ We have been dyingggg to do wall molding in our master bedroom and after watching about a dozen YouTube videos about it, we finally did it! Shoutout to my amazing husband who did majority of the work to make this a reality. 🤍🫶

Since the goal is to rent out this place when we leave Sheppard AFB, we are aiming to elevate our home and add touches that we LOVE but that will be desirable for our future renters too.

This was the first step in our bedroom transformation and I’m here to say that while the whole process from start to finish can look overwhelming, it was actually not too difficult and totally attainable AND sooooo worth putting in the extra work for if you’re already planning on painting your space!

Stay tuned for the finished product (once the rest of our furniture arrives) and if you have any ideas on how we should decorate the middle molding box go give your input over on my stories!! 🤗

💌 | Being intentional with every detail of our wedding, no matter how big or small has always been a priority to me. I want our wedding to feel grand, but at the same time intimate and timeless. 

To me, sending out save the dates set the tone of a wedding right from the beginning and I wanted our guests to feel the effort and love poured into the first piece of mail they receive from us. Designing our save the dates online and putting together each individual item by hand was something that has always been at the top of my “must do” list. (I am not a template girlie.)

Tilo and I both love to make things functional yet aesthetically pleasing at the same time. To check off both of those boxes, we decided to not print our wedding website details on the actual card and I created a QR code sticker to be placed on the vellum jackets. We both really wanted to have a wax seal incorporated into the mix but knew it wouldn’t hold up in the mail if it was on the outside of the envelope, so we pivoted to having a sticker wax seal hold together the vellum jackets and used a envelope sealer to keep the outside looking crisp. I hand addressed each envelope to add a personal touch and we opted for embossing on our return address to make things more simple.

Sticking with the functional yet aesthetic theme, we chose to include magnets with our wedding date and one of our favorite photos from our shoot at our venue with @garryandstacyphotographyco to add that extra touch.

The final touch to our save the dates was the stamp. After searching far and wide I found “Mountain Flora” Forever Stamps originally hand drawn by @liliarnoldstudios and then adapted digitally for stamp use. This design celebrates the beauty of mountain flowers which seemed perfectly fitting for a wedding taking place in the mountains of Asheville.

This mini wedding project has been my labor of love for months now and I am so happy that it finally came to life.🥹 Now onto the invites!

Closing out the month of June reflecting on these past six months of 2023: This was the year I finally took back control of living a life full of purpose and living for ME.🤍 A v vulnerable insta journal entry is below.🥹

Moving away from my hometown, family, and best friends in 2021 absolutely crushed me. I spent all of 2022 trying to figure out how to navigate this new and unknown life all while trying to plan a wedding that had been pushed back twice, working in a job I was unhappy with, and trying to find my people in a small town in Texas. I missed my old life and was mourning the past I said goodbye to, all while trying to be thankful for this new life. I became lethargic, gained too much sad girl weight, and would come home and just crash at the end of my day because I felt so lost. (All things people don’t see because social media is fake!) 

I decided that in this new year, 2023 was going to be the year  of “choosing me”. These past six months, I finally focused on putting my energy towards things that bring value to my life: seeing my best friends I haven’t seen in almost two years, going back home to see family, prioritizing my physical health, and taking weekend trips just to get away. I focused on being Sara. I have never been happier, felt more energized and motivated, and I have never felt more like ME.🤍 I have the most encouraging, sweet, angel human of a husband who has supported me so much in finding my happy again and I wouldn’t have had this much growth without him pushing me to just do all the things my heart desires.

While I do love and appreciate this mil life we live together here in Texas, it’s important for me to do me and feel like I am my own person, and I finally feel that way again.🤍 

If you’ve made it this far, remember that this is YOUR life to live. Live it to the fullest and put your energy towards things that make your soul shine.

#growth #personalgrowth #personalgrowthjourney

A Sunday reset for the kitchen🫶🥦🌽🍅✍️ We’re prepping for the new month ahead which means planning out meals + organizing the fridge and pantry with allllllll the things. 

I love love love to micromanage the kitchen situation. It makes for stress free weeks because we don’t even have to think about what we’re going to eat. 

It’s taken us almost a year, but we’ve finally figured out what meals we like most, our most used ingredients, what veggies to use first, and tricks to keep veggies lasting longer…. A love note to December… 💌 | Welcome to the first day of December, marking the beginning of the grand finale of the year. As we step into the last chapter of 2023, it’s a moment to reflect on the incredible journey we’ve embarked on. This year has been nothing short of amazing, a tapestry woven with dreams chased and moments lived to the fullest. From personal milestones to unexpected adventures, each day has added a unique hue to the canvas of our lives.
